## 5. Risks and Assumptions

### 5.1 Risks

|  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Risk | Impact | Likelihood | Mitigation |
| grep regex misses edge cases in parsing | Medium | High | Test with real-world projects; accept ≥80% accuracy |
| macOS vs Linux command differences | Medium | Medium | Platform detection at script start; test on both |
| JSON generation without jq may produce invalid JSON | High | Medium | Strict escaping functions; validate output in CI |
| Bash 4.0 not available on older macOS (ships Bash 3.2) | Medium | Medium | Document requirement; suggest brew install bash for macOS < 14 |
| Large projects (10k+ files) may be slow in Bash | Medium | Low | Optimize with find -exec batching; accept slower than Python/TS |

### 5.2 Assumptions

* Target machines have Bash 4.0+ (Linux default; macOS 14+ or Homebrew bash)
* Standard POSIX utilities are available and on PATH
* Source code files use UTF-8 encoding (or indexer skips non-UTF-8)
* Project root contains build files at top level or one level deep
* Output directory .analysis/code-intelligence/ can be created if missing
* Output format MUST be compatible with existing TypeScript/Python indexer outputs

## 6. Non-Functional Requirements

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Category | Requirement | Target |
| Performance | Index 1000-file project | < 60 seconds |
| Performance | Index 100-file project | < 10 seconds |
| Portability | Cross-platform | Linux (Ubuntu 22.04+), macOS (13+) |
| Portability | Shell compatibility | Bash 4.0+ |
| Maintainability | Script modularity | Separate sourced files by responsibility |
| Reliability | Error handling | Never crash on bad input; exit codes for errors |
| Compatibility | Output format | Identical to Python/TypeScript indexer output |

