## 8. Appendix

### Output File Specifications

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| File | Format | Purpose |
| project-structure.md | Markdown | Human-readable project overview |
| index-metadata.json | JSON | Machine-readable file metadata with content hashes |
| kb-payloads.json | JSON array | Ready-to-ingest KB documents |
| modules/{name}.md | Markdown | Per-module detailed analysis |

### Supported File Extensions

|  |  |
| --- | --- |
| Language | Extensions |
| Kotlin | .kt, .kts |
| Java | .java |
| Python | .py |
| TypeScript | .ts, .tsx |
| JavaScript | .js, .jsx |
| Go | .go |
| Rust | .rs |

### Default Exclusions

* node\_modules/, build/, dist/, .gradle/, target/
* .git/, .idea/, .vscode/, \_\_pycache\_\_/
* Binary files, generated files

### Platform Compatibility Matrix

|  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Feature | Linux (Ubuntu 22.04+) | macOS 13+ | macOS < 13 |
| Bash 4.0+ | ✅ Built-in | ✅ (macOS 14+) or Homebrew | ❌ Needs Homebrew |
| sha256sum | ✅ coreutils | ❌ Use shasum -a 256 | ❌ Use shasum -a 256 |
| grep -E | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ |
| find -maxdepth | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ |
| awk | ✅ gawk | ✅ BSD awk | ✅ BSD awk |
| sed -i | ✅ sed -i '' not needed | ⚠️ Needs sed -i '' | ⚠️ Needs sed -i '' |

### Script File Organization

.analysis/code-intelligence/scripts/bash/
├── index.sh ← Entry point (orchestration)
├── config.sh ← Configuration loading (index-config.json parsing)
├── detector.sh ← Project type detection
├── discovery.sh ← Module discovery
├── scanner.sh ← File scanning + filtering
├── parser.sh ← Source file parsing (grep patterns)
├── generator.sh ← Output file generation (JSON, Markdown)
└── utils.sh ← Shared utilities (hash, path helpers, JSON escape)

### Glossary

|  |  |
| --- | --- |
| Term | Definition |
| Code Intelligence | Structured metadata about source code for AI consumption |
| KB Payload | JSON object ready for ingestion into knowledge base |
| Module | A logical grouping of source files (package, subproject, directory) |
| Signature | Function/class declaration without implementation body |
| POSIX | Portable Operating System Interface — standard for Unix-like systems |

